Execute only PHASE 09.1.

Goal:
Fix production-hardening gaps discovered after Phase 08 + Phase 7.10 before adding new Enterprise Cloud Scale features.

Scope:
1. Add/verify PostgreSQL runtime driver:
   - backend/pyproject.toml
   - backend/requirements.txt
   Add psycopg[binary]>=3.2.0 if missing.

2. Harden collaboration WebSocket:
   - backend/app/collaboration/router.py
   - When AUTH_ENABLED=true, require valid access token.
   - Accept token via query param token=... or compatible WebSocket handshake/subprotocol.
   - Decode token using existing JWT utilities.
   - Close invalid/missing auth with policy violation code.
   - Preserve dev behavior when AUTH_ENABLED=false.

3. Harden workspace federation:
   - backend/app/api/workspaces.py
   - Keep /status public if useful.
   - Protect /peers and /register with auth/RBAC.
   - Add Pydantic model for register payload.
   - Validate name length.
   - Keep mode mock-only/dry-run.
   - Do not perform outbound network calls.

4. Harden frontend WebSocket base URL:
   - Add optional VITE_WS_BASE_URL.
   - Otherwise derive ws/wss from VITE_API_BASE_URL.
   - Do not depend only on window.location.origin.
   - Keep fallback behavior.

5. Add tests:
   - backend collaboration websocket auth test if practical
   - backend federation auth test
   - frontend WS URL helper test

Rules:
- Keep backend port 8005.
- Never use localhost:8000.
- No secrets.
- No real external actions.
- No autopep8 --aggressive.

Validation:
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
python -B -m pytest -q

cd ../frontend
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh
nvm use 20
npm test
npm run build

cd ..
docker build -f infra/docker/backend.Dockerfile .
docker build -f infra/docker/frontend.Dockerfile .
docker build -f infra/docker/nginx.Dockerfile .
docker compose config
docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml config

Commit:
fix(prod): harden collaboration auth and postgres runtime